{{Infobox mountain | name = Mount San Cristobal | other_name = | photo = Mount San Cristobal.jpg | photo_size = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 1470 | elevation_ref = <ref name="pinoymountaineer" /> | prominence_m = | prominence_ref = | listing = [[List of potentially active volcanoes in the Philippines|Potentially active]]<ref name="PHIVOLCS">{{cite web|title=Potentially Active|url=http://www.phivolcs.dost.gov.ph/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=60:potentially-active&catid=55&Itemid=115|website=[[Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology]]|accessdate=24 March 2016|date=30 July 2008}}</ref> | range = | parent_peak = | location = [[Luzon]] | map = Philippines | map_alt = | map_caption = Location within the Philippines | map_relief = | map_size = | label = Mount {{nowrap|San Cristobal}} | label_position = left | coordinates = {{coord|14.06443|N|121.42680|E|type:mountain_region:PH_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | coordinates_ref = | country = [[Philippines]] | state = [[CALABARZON]] | state_type = Region | region = {{hlist | [[Laguna (province)|Laguna]] | [[Quezon]] }} | region_type = Provinces | city = {{hlist | [[Dolores, Quezon|Dolores]] | [[San Pablo, Laguna|San Pablo]] }} | city_type = Municipalities | topo = | type = [[Complex volcano]] | volcanic_arc/belt = Macolod Corridor | age = | last_eruption = Unknown | first_ascent = | easiest_route = from Dolores, Quezon }}
'''Mount San Cristobal''' is a [[dormant volcano|dormant]] [[volcano]] in [[Quezon province]] on the island of [[Luzon]], [[Philippines]]. The mountain rises to an elevation of {{convert|1470|m|abbr=on}} [[above mean sea level]] <ref name="pinoymountaineer" /> and is one of the volcanic features of [[Macolod Corridor]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Tectonophysics|date=1990|publisher=Elsevier Science Publishers|location=Amsterdam|page=266}}</ref>
Mount San Cristobal is considered the Devil's mountain in Filipino folklore. It is the alter-ego of the Holy Mountain,<ref name=pinoymountaineer>{{cite web|title=Mt. Cristobal (1,470+)|url=http://www.pinoymountaineer.com/2007/09/mt-cristobal-1470.html|website=Pinoy Mountaineer|accessdate=5 February 2015|date=23 September 2007}}</ref> [[Mount Banahaw]], and is part of [[Mounts Banahaw–San Cristobal Protected Landscape]] covering 10,901 hectares (26,940 acres) of land.
The mountain is bounded by [[San Pablo, Laguna|San Pablo]], province of [[Laguna (province)|Laguna]] at its northern slope and [[Dolores, Quezon|Dolores]], province of [[Quezon (province)|Quezon]] at its southern slope.
[[File:Seven Lakes of San Pablo.jpg|thumb|none|7 lakes of San Pablo City, Laguna as seen from the top of Mt. San Cristobal at 1470 meters above sea level.]]
